column8: Amoxyclav 625 Tablet contains a combination of two medicines Amoxicillin and Clavulanic acid. It belongs to class of penicillin antibiotics. It is used for the treatment of various bacterial infections such as infection of lungs, airways, ears, urinary tract, skin, bone, joints, soft tissue and tooth. Amoxyclav 625 Tablet works by combined action of its two components. Amoxicillin kills the bacteria which are responsible for infections and Clavulanic acid helps in maintaining an optimal level of Amoxicillin by inactivating the enzymes which break the Amoxicillin. Please inform your doctor if you are allergic to antibiotics or have experienced any allergic reaction after taking antibiotics. This medicine should not be used during pregnancy, especially in the first trimester.read less

It is also useful to treat symptoms such as allergy due to dust, pet allergies and insect bite. Allergic symptoms appear due to the production of a chemical in the body, namely Histamine. Xevor 5mg Tablet works by blocking the actions of Histamine. Do not use it if you are allergic to Levocetirizine. Avoid driving and handling any machinery, as this medicine makes you less alert.read less

column8: Duphaston tablet contains dydrogesterone as an active ingredient. It is a synthetic form of the female hormone progesterone. Duphaston is an original research brand of Dydrogesterone, first approved in April 1960. Dydrogesterone granules present in Duphaston are manufactured in Weesp, Netherlands and are tableted in two states of-the-art manufacturing sites in India. Duphaston tablets are used to treat disorders related to the female reproductive cycle, infertility, irregular menses and uterine bleeding. It works by imitating the actions of the natural hormone progesterone and hence improves the conditions that occur due to imbalance in the hormonal levels. Before starting the treatment with this medicine for abnormal uterine bleeding, the cause for abnormal bleeding should be identified. This medicine may cause breakthrough bleeding and spotting during the initial days of the treatment. If this continues, then inform your doctor.read less

Junior Lanzol 15 mg Tablet contains Lansoprazole, which belongs to a class of medicine called “Proton pump inhibitors”, medications used to reduce the amount of acid produced in the stomach. This tablet is used for relieving acidity and heartburn in conditions such as stomach and intestinal ulcers, acid reflux disease and Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome. It works by blocking the micropumps in stomach cells which are responsible for acid production. Take this medicine 30 minutes before taking food. Use this medicine cautiously in patients with osteoporosis, diarrhoea, hypomagnesemia and liver problems. Diarrhoea, gas, headache, nausea are some common side effects this medicine, consult your doctor if these symptoms persist or worsen.
